TITLE: Custom Escaping in PHP for SilverStripe
DESCRIPTION: Shows manual escaping techniques in PHP using SilverStripe's Convert class when preparing HTML outputs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/silverstripe/developer-docs/blob/5/en/02_Developer_Guides/09_Security/05_Secure_Coding.md#2025-04-21_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
namespace App\Control;

use SilverStripe\Control\Controller;
use SilverStripe\Core\Convert;
use SilverStripe\ORM\FieldType\DBHTMLText;
use SilverStripe\ORM\FieldType\DBText;

class MyController extends Controller
{
    private static $allowed_actions = ['search'];

    public function search($request)
    {
        $htmlTitle = '<p>Your results for:' . Convert::raw2xml($request->getVar('Query')) . '</p>';
        return $this->customise([
            'Query' => DBText::create($request->getVar('Query')),
            'HTMLTitle' => DBHTMLText::create($htmlTitle),
        ]);
    }
}

```

