TITLE: Custom Application Actions in Silverstripe CMS (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to execute custom application actions using the `Application::execute()` method in Silverstripe CMS.  It sets up a request, session, and controller, but leaves the application in a 'ready' state without performing any routing. Dependencies include CLIRequestBuilder, TestKernel, HTTPApplication, HTTPRequest and Controller.
