TITLE: Using i18n::_t in PHP Files
DESCRIPTION: This example showcases the usage of `i18n::_t` in PHP files for string translation, variable injection, and pluralization. It demonstrates how to translate simple strings, inject variables into translated strings, and invoke plural forms using a pipe delimiter and a {count} argument. The snippet also shows referencing the current class name.
SOURCE: https://github.com/silverstripe/developer-docs/blob/5/en/02_Developer_Guides/13_i18n/index.md#2025-04-21_snippet_8

