TITLE: Implementing $* Wildcard URL Handler in SilverStripe PHP Controller
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the '$*' wildcard URL pattern to match all URL parameters without collecting them individually.
SOURCE: https://github.com/silverstripe/developer-docs/blob/5/en/02_Developer_Guides/02_Controllers/02_Routing.md#2025-04-21_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
namespace App\Control;

use SilverStripe\Control\Controller;
use SilverStripe\Control\HTTPRequest;

class StaffController extends Controller
{
    private static $url_handlers = [
        '$*' => 'index',
    ];

    public function index(HTTPRequest $request)
    {
        // GET /staff/managers/bob/hobbies
        // "managers/bob/hobbies"
        $request->remaining();

        // returns "managers", and removes that from the list of remaining params
        $nextParam = $request->shift();

        // returns ["bob", "hobbies"] and removes those from the list of remaining params
        $moreParams = $request->shift(2);
    }
}
```

