TITLE: Explicitly Revoking File Access in Silverstripe Controller
DESCRIPTION: PHP code showing how to explicitly revoke access to files in a PageController. This example grants access if the user has view permissions, otherwise revokes any historical grants.
SOURCE: https://github.com/silverstripe/developer-docs/blob/5/en/02_Developer_Guides/14_Files/03_File_Security.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
namespace {
    use SilverStripe\CMS\Controllers\ContentController;

    class PageController extends ContentController
    {
        public function init()
        {
            parent::init();

            // Whitelist the protected files on this page for the current user
            $file = $this->File();
            if ($file->canView()) {
                $file->grantFile();
            } else {
                // Will revoke any historical grants
                $file->revokeFile();
            }
        }
    }
}
```

